Microsoft is rolling out the Surface Book 2 to more countries, of which South Africa is not one of them. The 15-inch Surface Book 2 will be available in Australia, Austria, Belgium, Canada, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Ireland, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, New Zealand, Norway, Poland, Sweden, Switzerland, and the United Kingdom. From February, March, and April, the Surface Book 2 13-inch and 15-inch models will roll out to Bahrain, China, Hong Kong, India, Italy, Korea, Kuwait, Malaysia, Oman, Portugal, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Singapore, Spain, Taiwan, Thailand, and the United Arab Emirates. The announcement comes after Microsoft SA told MyBroadband that the Surface Book 2 will not be officially available in South Africa.